    "rationale": "With a strict linear \u03c4-chain, only one task is ever ready and N parallel workers all collide on it. To enable parallel work, the queue exposes 5 independent ready tasks: the head of the \u03b3=4 \u03c4-walk (g400_t1000), two \u03b3-sweep roots that warm-start directly from the seed (g025_t0200, g200_t0200), and three lognormal no-learning tasks that need no REE warm-start at all. Each new \u03c4-walk completion unblocks its successor; the lognormal tasks are independent and self-contained."
  },
  "deps_semantics": {
    "default": "all",
    "any": "Tasks may declare deps_satisfy='any', meaning the task is ready as soon as ANY listed dependency is done. Used when a worker can warm-start from one of several nearby checkpoints (e.g. g200_t0200 from either g100_t0200 or g400_t0200)."
  },
  "notes": [
    "\u03b3=0.5 high-\u03c4 (\u03c4 \u2265 4) bailed; the 7-point \u03b3=0.5 curve (\u03c4\u2208[0.3,3.0]) is the accepted answer for Fig 4A.",
    "\u03b3=1.0 high-\u03c4 (\u03c4 \u2265 5) bailed; the 8-point \u03b3=1.0 curve (\u03c4\u2208[0.3,4.0]) is the accepted answer.",
    "\u03b3=4.0 sweep: \u03c4 \u2208 [0.3, 7.0] done. Only \u03c4=10 is ready and \u03c4=15 is blocked on it.",
    "\u03b3=0.25 and \u03b3=2.0 \u03c4-sweeps added as parallel chains: their \u03c4=2 root warm-starts from the seed and runs concurrently with the \u03b3=4 tail.",
    "Three lognormal Fig R2 tasks (\u03b3=0.5, 1.0, 4.0) are self-contained no-learning runs \u2014 no REE warm-start, run anywhere.",
    "All 1-R\u00b2 values are weighted by ex-ante probability (see EQUATIONS.md \u00a77).",
    "Checkpoints listed for done tasks are the expected paths; if a path is missing on disk, the underlying run was completed but the per-task checkpoint was not committed back to results/full_ree/. The summary numbers come from results/full_ree/fig4A_G20_tau_sweep.json / fig4B_G20_gamma_sweep.json."
  ]
